  m_ParameterInfo:
  - name: Grids
    path: 
    tooltip: 
    space: -1
    spaceable: 0
    sheetType: 
    realType: 
    defaultValue:
      m_Type:
        m_SerializableType: 
      m_SerializableObject: 
    min: -Infinity
    max: Infinity
    enumValues: []
    descendantCount: 0
  - name: bounds
    path: bounds
    tooltip: The size of the box that defines the bounding of the effect. The larger
      it is, the more particles there will be and so an overhead is to be expected.
    space: -1
    spaceable: 0
    sheetType: m_Float
    realType: Single
    defaultValue:
      m_Type:
        m_SerializableType: System.Single, mscorlib, Version=4.0.0.0, Culture=neutral,
          PublicKeyToken=b77a5c561934e089
      m_SerializableObject: 300
    min: -Infinity
    max: Infinity
    enumValues: []
    descendantCount: 0
  - name: primaryStep
    path: primaryStep
    tooltip: The length of the primary grid division. (The invisible particles in
      the primary grid read the ocean state at their position) If too high, some
      waves might not break, too small there will be a GPU overhead.
    space: -1
    spaceable: 0
    sheetType: m_Float
    realType: Single
    defaultValue:
      m_Type:
        m_SerializableType: System.Single, mscorlib, Version=4.0.0.0, Culture=neutral,
          PublicKeyToken=b77a5c561934e089
      m_SerializableObject: 2
    min: 0
    max: 10
    enumValues: []
    descendantCount: 0
  - name: secondaryStep
    path: secondaryStep
    tooltip: The length of the secondary random grid relative to the wave size that
      triggers it. This defines the density of burst particles generated.
    space: -1
    spaceable: 0
    sheetType: m_Float
    realType: Single
    defaultValue:
      m_Type:
        m_SerializableType: System.Single, mscorlib, Version=4.0.0.0, Culture=neutral,
          PublicKeyToken=b77a5c561934e089
      m_SerializableObject: 0.1
    min: 0
    max: 0.5
    enumValues: []
    descendantCount: 0
  - name: primaryTrigger
    path: primaryTrigger
    tooltip: The water compression that triggers the creation of the secondary grid
      by the primary grid. If too low the primary grid might miss some breakers,
      if too high their will be too much of the secondary grid creation and an overhead
      is to be expected.
    space: -1
    spaceable: 0
    sheetType: m_Float
    realType: Single
    defaultValue:
      m_Type:
        m_SerializableType: System.Single, mscorlib, Version=4.0.0.0, Culture=neutral,
          PublicKeyToken=b77a5c561934e089
      m_SerializableObject: 0.5
    min: 0
    max: 2.5
    enumValues: []
    descendantCount: 0
  - name: secondaryTrigger
    path: secondaryTrigger
    tooltip: The water compression that makes the particles of the seocndary grid
      alive and render sea foam burst. The smaller the value, the longer the waves
      will break.
    space: -1
    spaceable: 0
    sheetType: m_Float
    realType: Single
    defaultValue:
